Nominated MP David ole Sanko want top National Transport and Safety Authority to resign, saying they have been unable to restore sanity on Kenyan roads. He accused them of collecting bribes from drivers and risking the lives of passengers At least  250 people have perished in road accidents across the country in December alone. Read more : NTSA bans PSV night travel after Salgaa crash Speaking to the media at Osim Country Lodge in Narok town yesterday, he said the move by the authority to suspend licenses of reckless drivers would not help since the vehicles would find their way back on the roads.  “The authority was set up is to prevent accidents, but it has failed because its staff has turned the agency into a cash cow,” Sankok, who represent persons living with disability, said. Click here for latest political news